---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---
<section id="docs" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="section-title">DOCUMENTATION</h2>
    <div style="text-align:center; margin-bottom:2rem">
        <a
            href={`${base}/docs`}
            class="docs-view-btn"
            style="display:inline-block; padding:0.75rem 2rem; background:var(--accent); color:var(--bg); font-family:var(--pixel); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:700; text-decoration:none; border-radius:6px; letter-spacing:0.02em; transition:background 0.2s;"
        >
            View full documentation &rarr;
        </a>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-grid">
        <a class="doc-card" href="https://github.com/jonathanperis/super-mango-editor#readme" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Read the project README on GitHub">
            <h3>README</h3>
            <p>Project overview, build instructions for all platforms, controls reference, architecture diagram, and full project structure.</p>
        </a>
        <!-- Engine & Code -->
        <a class="doc-card" href={`${base}/docs/architecture/`} aria-label="Read the Architecture section">
            <h3>Architecture</h3>
            <p>Startup sequence, game loop phases, coordinate system, GameState struct, and error handling strategy.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="doc-card" href={`${base}/docs/source-files/`} aria-label="Read the Source Files section">
            <h3>Source Files</h3>
            <p>Complete file map of all source files with descriptions of main.c, game.h, game.c, and every module role.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="doc-card" href={`${base}/docs/player-module/`} aria-label="Read the Player Module section">
            <h3>Player Module</h3>
            <p>Player lifecycle, input handling, jump and climb logic, physics update, animation state machine.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="doc-card" href={`${base}/docs/constants-reference/`} aria-label="Read the Constants Reference section">
            <h3>Constants Reference</h3>
            <p>All compile-time constants: window, canvas, timing, tiles, physics, camera, and player locals.</p>
        </a>
        <!-- Content & Assets -->
        <a class="doc-card" href={`${base}/docs/entities-and-hazards/`} aria-label="Read the Entities & Hazards section">
            <h3>Entities & Hazards</h3>
            <p>Six enemy types and seven hazard types: spider, bird, fish, spikes, circular saw, axe trap, and more.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="doc-card" href={`${base}/docs/collectibles-and-surfaces/`} aria-label="Read the Collectibles & Surfaces section">
            <h3>Collectibles & Surfaces</h3>
            <p>Coins, stars, platforms, bouncepads, vines, ladders, ropes — everything the player collects or stands on.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="doc-card" href={`${base}/docs/assets/`} aria-label="Read the Assets section">
            <h3>Assets</h3>
            <p>Sprite catalog, player sprite sheet analysis, animation row mapping, and asset organization.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="doc-card" href={`${base}/docs/sounds/`} aria-label="Read the Sounds section">
            <h3>Sounds</h3>
            <p>Sound effects catalog, audio configuration, Mix_Chunk vs Mix_Music, and adding new sound effects.</p>
        </a>
        <!-- Building & Contributing -->
        <a class="doc-card" href={`${base}/docs/build-system/`} aria-label="Read the Build System section">
            <h3>Build System</h3>
            <p>Makefile overview, compiler flags, build targets for macOS, Linux, Windows, and WebAssembly.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="doc-card" href={`${base}/docs/level-design/`} aria-label="Read the Level Design section">
            <h3>Level Design</h3>
            <p>TOML level file format reference: entities, collectibles, hazards, surfaces, and level metadata.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="doc-card" href={`${base}/docs/level-editor/`} aria-label="Read the Level Editor section">
            <h3>Level Editor</h3>
            <p>Visual level editor guide: canvas, palette, tools, properties panel, undo history, and export.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="doc-card" href={`${base}/docs/developer-guide/`} aria-label="Read the Developer Guide section">
            <h3>Developer Guide</h3>
            <p>Coding conventions, naming rules, memory safety, and step-by-step entity addition walkthrough.</p>
        </a>
    </div>
</section>
